  "prompt": "How soon after implantation bleeding would a test be negative?",
  "response": "Implantation bleeding typically occurs 10-14 days after conception. A home pregnancy test may still show a negative result immediately after implantation bleeding. For the most accurate results, it's recommended to wait until after a missed period, which is usually about 14-16 days after conception. Taking a test too early can result in a false negative. For the most reliable result, wait until the first day of a missed period or about 1-2 weeks after implantation bleeding.",
